text: NCBI uses search term syntax can associated specific search field enclosed pair square brackets. , instance "Homo sapiens[ORGN]" denotes search Homo sapiens “Organism” field. Details see https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/geo/info/qqtutorial.html. can use term query desirable results geo_search. geo_search parse searching results return data.frame object containing records based search term. internal geo_search based rentrez package, provides functions working NCBI Eutils API, can utilize NCBI API key increase downloading speed, details see https://docs.ropensci.org/rentrez/articles/rentrez_tutorial.html#rate-limiting--api-keys. Providing want GSE GEO records related human diabetes, can get records following code, returned object data.frame: , can use whatever ’re famaliar filter searching results. Providing want GSE datasets least 6 diabetic nephropathy samples containing expression profiling. example code: filtering, got 36 candidate datasets. can reduce lot time us comparing refining datasets reading summary records.

title: Tools for Accessing and Working with the Gene Expression Omnibus (GEO)
text: GEO database mainly provides SOFT (Simple Omnibus Format Text) formatted files GPL, GSM GDS entity. SOFT designed rapid batch submission download data. SOFT simple line-based, plain text format, meaning SOFT files may readily generated common spreadsheet database applications. single SOFT file can hold data tables accompanying descriptive information multiple, concatenated Platforms, Samples, /Series records. geokit provide GEOSoft class object store SOFT file contents, GEOSoft object contains four slots (“accession”, “meta”, “datatable”, “columns”). accession slot stores GEO accession ID, meta slot contains metadata header SOFT formatted file, datatable slot contains data table SOFT file main data us use, along columns slot providing descriptive column header datatable data. can use function name slots extract data. geo can download SOFT files preprocess well, example code get soft file GPL, GSM GDS entity respectively. GSE entity, also soft file associated . structure different GPL, GSM GDS entity, geokit provide GEOSeries class keep contents GSE soft file. Actually, GSE soft file contains almost contents subsets soft file including GPL GSM, GEOSeries class provides gpl gsm slots list GEOSoft. download GSE soft file, just set gse_matrix FALSE geo function. ’s common use series matrix file usual analysis workflow, can also handle easily geokit, need just set gse_matrix TRUE geo function, also default value. gse_matrix TRUE, geo return ExpressionSet object can interact lots Bioconductor packages. two parameters controling processing details parsing series matrix file. parsing phenoData series matrix files directly, ’s common fail discern characteristics_ch* columns, contain important traits informations corresponding samples, since many characteristics_ch* columns series matrix files often lacks separate strings. pdata_from_soft, indicates whether retrieve phenoData GEO Soft file, can help handle problem well. soft file large don’t want use , can set pdata_from_soft FALSE use parse_pdata function parse manully. Another important parameter add_gpl, FALSE indicates geo try map current GPL accession id Bioconductor annotation package, can use latest bioconductor annotation package get --date featureData, otherwise, geo add featureData GPL soft file directly.

text: GEOData class, contains two slots meta accession, basic class (super class) GEOSeries class GEOSoft class. GEOSeries class contains extra two slots gsm gpl special GSE entity soft file GEOSoft contains extra two slots columns datatable special GEO samples, platforms, datasets.

title: Virtual class for holding GEO series, samples, platforms, and datasets. — GEO-class
text: meta: list, containing header metadata informations. accession: character giving geo accession id current GEO series, samples, platforms, datasets. columns: data.frame gives datatable header descriptions. rownmaes data.frame column names slot datatable. datatable: data.frame shows data information. gsm: list GEOSoft object containg samples information current GEO series. gpl: list GEOSoft object containg platforms information current GEO series.

what: Retrieve GEO Objects from NCBI GEO — geo
title: Retrieve GEO Objects from NCBI GEO — geo
text: main user-facing function geokit package. downloads parses GEO files, returning objects corresponding different GEO entity types. geo() allows programmatic access NCBI GEO data. GEO stores high-throughput experimental data, including microarrays, SAGE, mass spectrometry proteomics. Entities handled geo() include: Platform (GPLxxx): Defines probe elements detectable molecules. Sample (GSMxxx): Describes conditions measurements individual samples. Series (GSExxx): Groups related samples, describing experimental context. DataSet (GDSxxx): Curated sets comparable samples. function downloads parses relevant SOFT Series Matrix files, optionally mapping platform IDs Bioconductor annotation packages.

title: Retrieve GEO Objects from NCBI GEO — geo
code: geo(   ids,   amount = NULL,   gse_matrix = TRUE,   pdata_from_soft = TRUE,   add_gpl = NULL,   ftp_over_https = TRUE,   handle_opts = list(),   odir = getwd() )

title: Retrieve GEO Objects from NCBI GEO — geo
text: ids Character vector GEO accession IDs download parse. IDs must belong GEO entity type. Examples: DataSets: c("GDS505", "GDS606") Series: c("GSE2", "GSE22") amount character string specifying amount data retrieve. One "brief", "quick", "data", "full", "soft", "soft_full": "brief": shows accession's attributes. "quick": shows accession's attributes first 20 rows data table. "full": shows accession's attributes complete data table. default ids DataSets Series. "data": omits accession's attributes, showing links accessions full data table. "soft": SOFT (Simple Omnibus Text Format) GEO FTP site. ids DataSets Series, default. "soft_full": full SOFT (Simple Omnibus Text Format) files GEO FTP site DataSet (GDS) containging additionally contains --date gene annotation DataSet Platform. DataSet, "data" "full" mapped "soft" "soft_full" respectively. gse_matrix Logical, whether retrieve Series Matrix files GSE entities. TRUE, ExpressionSet returned. pdata_from_soft Logical, whether derive phenoData GSE series SOFT file creating ExpressionSet.  Defaults TRUE. FALSE, phenoData parsed series matrix file; note characteristics_ch* columns may parse correctly. add_gpl Logical NULL. Whether include platform information (featureData slot) handling GSE entities gse_matrix = TRUE. NULL (default), function attempts map GPL accession Bioconductor annotation package. successful, annotation slot updated add_gpl set FALSE; otherwise, add_gpl set TRUE. ftp_over_https Logical scalar. TRUE, connects GEO FTP via HTTPS (https://ftp.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/geo); otherwise, uses plain FTP. handle_opts list named options / headers set multi_download. odir Destination directory downloads. Defaults current working directory.

title: Retrieve GEO Objects from NCBI GEO — geo
text: Returns object corresponding GEO entity type: GSE gse_matrix = FALSE: GEOSeries object. GSE gse_matrix = TRUE: ExpressionSet list ExpressionSets, one per Series Matrix file. entities: GEOSoft object.

title: Retrieve GEO Objects from NCBI GEO — geo
text: Gene Expression Omnibus (GEO) NCBI serves public repository wide range high-throughput experimental data. data include single dual channel microarray-based experiments measuring mRNA, genomic DNA, protein abundance, well non-array techniques serial analysis gene expression (SAGE), mass spectrometry proteomic data. basic level organization GEO, three entity types may supplied users: Platforms, Samples, Series. Additionally, curated entity called GEO dataset. Platform record describes list elements array (e.g., cDNAs, oligonucleotide probesets, ORFs, antibodies) list elements may detected quantified experiment (e.g., SAGE tags, peptides). Platform record assigned unique stable GEO accession number (GPLxxx). Platform may reference many Samples submitted multiple submitters. Sample record describes conditions individual Sample handled, manipulations underwent, abundance measurement element derived . Sample record assigned unique stable GEO accession number (GSMxxx). Sample entity must reference one Platform may included multiple Series. Series record defines set related Samples considered part group, Samples related, ordered. Series provides focal point description experiment whole. Series records may also contain tables describing extracted data, summary conclusions, analyses. Series record assigned unique stable GEO accession number (GSExxx). GEO DataSets (GDSxxx) curated sets GEO Sample data. GDS record represents collection biologically statistically comparable GEO Samples forms basis GEO's suite data display analysis tools. Samples within GDS refer Platform, , share common set probe elements. Value measurements Sample within GDS assumed calculated equivalent manner, , considerations background processing normalization consistent across dataset. Information reflecting experimental design provided GDS subsets.

text: Determine type GEO accession ID (e.g. DataSet, Series, Sample, Platform). function inspects accession prefix returns corresponding GEO type, optionally abbreviated form.

title: GEO accession type — geo_gtype
text: accession character GEO accession IDs. Examples: DataSets (GDS): "GDS505", "GDS606", "GDS1234", "GDS9999", etc. Series (GSE): "GSE2", "GSE22", "GSE100", "GSE2000", etc. Platforms (GPL): "GPL96", "GPL570", "GPL10558", etc. Samples (GSM): "GSM12345", "GSM67890", "GSM112233", etc. abbre logical scalar indicating whether abbreviate GEO type return value. FALSE (default), full type name returned; TRUE, short abbreviation used.

text: Search GDS database return search results data.table.

title: Search GEO database — geo_search
code: geo_search(query, step = 500L, interval = NULL)

title: Search GEO database — geo_search
text: query character string search term. NCBI uses fielded search syntax. example, "Homo sapiens[ORGN]" searches "Organism" field Homo sapiens. See GEO query tutorial details. Searchable fields can listed rentrez::entrez_db_searchable("gds"). step Integer. Number records fetch per request. Use smaller value requests fail. interval Numeric. Time interval (seconds) successive requests. Defaults 0. Increase value requests fail due rate limits.

title: Search GEO database — geo_search
text: data.table contains search results

title: Search GEO database — geo_search
text: NCBI allows higher request limits (10 per second) using API key. can set key current R session rentrez::set_entrez_key(), permanently setting ENTREZ_KEY environment variable via Sys.setenv(). set, rentrez automatically use key NCBI requests. See rentrez tutorial details.

Examples: DataSets (GDS): "GDS505", "GDS606", "GDS1234", "GDS9999", etc. Series (GSE): "GSE2", "GSE22", "GSE100", "GSE2000", etc. Platforms (GPL): "GPL96", "GPL570", "GPL10558", etc. Samples (GSM): "GSM12345", "GSM67890", "GSM112233", etc. famount character specifying file/amount type requested. GEO data can accessed two sites: Direct FTP/HTTPS file retrieval GEO FTP server (file type): "soft": SOFT (Simple Omnibus Text Format) GEO FTP site. accession DataSets Series, default. "soft_full": full SOFT (Simple Omnibus Text Format) files GEO FTP site DataSet (GDS) containging additionally contains --date gene annotation DataSet Platform. "minimal": MINiML (MIAME Notation Markup Language, pronounced minimal) XML format incorporates experimental data metadata. MINiML essentially XML rendering SOFT format. "matrix": Series matrix file. "annot": annotation files Platforms. "suppl": supplementary files. following table summarizes compatibility GEO accession types famount options: Accession-based queries NCBI GEO database (amount data): "none": Applicable DataSets; DataSets, also sole valid option. "brief": accession attributes . "quick": accession attributes + first 20 rows data table. "data": omits accession's attributes, showing links accessions full data table. "full": accession attributes + complete data table. scope character specifying GEO accessions include (applicable NCBI GEO database access). "none": Applicable DataSets; DataSets, also sole valid option "self": queried accession . "gsm", "gpl", "gse": related samples, platforms, series. "": accessions related query (family view). over_https Logical scalar. TRUE, connects GEO FTP server via HTTPS (https://ftp.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/geo); otherwise uses plain FTP (ftp://ftp.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/geo). applicable GEO FTP server access. browser non-empty character string giving name     program used HTML browser.  PATH,     full path specified.  Alternatively, R function     called invoke browser. Windows NULL also allowed (default),     implies file association mechanism used.

title: Get Supplemental Files from GEO — geo_suppl
text: NCBI GEO allows supplemental files attached GEO Series (GSE), GEO platforms (GPL), GEO samples (GSM). function 'knows' get files based GEO accession. parsing downloaded files attempted, since file format generally knowable computer.

Examples: DataSets: c("GDS505", "GDS606") Series: c("GSE2", "GSE22") pattern character string containing regular expression matched supplementary file names. ftp_over_https Logical scalar. TRUE, connects GEO FTP via HTTPS (https://ftp.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/geo); otherwise, uses plain FTP. handle_opts list named options / headers set multi_download. odir Destination directory downloads. title: Parse key-value pairs in GEO series matrix file — parse_pdata
code: parse_pdata(data, columns = NULL, sep = ":", split = ";")

title: Parse key-value pairs in GEO series matrix file — parse_pdata
text: data data.frame like object, tibble data.table also okay. columns character vector, ended "(ch\d*)(\.\d*)?". columns data parsed. NULL, columns started "characteristics_ch" used. sep string separating paired key-value, usually ":". split Passed strsplit function. Default ";"`.

title: Parse key-value pairs in GEO series matrix file — parse_pdata
text: modified data.frame.

title: Parse key-value pairs in GEO series matrix file — parse_pdata
text: characteristics annotation column usually contains multiple key-value items, first split columns split extract key-value pairs. new column added whose name first group "(ch\d*)(\.\d*)?$" regex pattern orginal column name connected key element key-value pair string "_" new column value character vector value element key-value pair.
